org.modelio.gproject.fragment.ramcfile

Class RamcFileFragment

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelio.gproject.fragment.AbstractFragment
      • org.modelio.gproject.fragment.ramcfile.RamcFileFragment
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IProjectFragment
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MdaFragment

    public class RamcFileFragment
extends AbstractFragment
    RAMC fragment stored in a .ramc file.

    The RAMC archive is extracted to the data directory on mounting.

      • doMountInitRepository

        protected IRepository doMountInitRepository(IModelioProgress aMonitor)
                                     throws IOException
        Description copied from class: AbstractFragment
        Instantiate the repository.

        This is a hook called by AbstractFragment.mount(GProject, IModelioProgress). The implementation must just instantiate the IRepository without opening it.

        The implementation must not call done() on the given monitor and must leave a non negligible part of the progress unconsumed.

        Specified by:
        doMountInitRepository in class AbstractFragment
        Parameters:
        aMonitor - the progress monitor to use for reporting progress to the user.

        The implementation must not call done() the given monitor and must leave a non negligible part of the progress unconsumed.

        Accepts null, indicating that no progress should be reported and that the operation cannot be cancelled.

        Returns:
        the instantiated repository.
        Throws:
        IOException - in case of failure.
